The paper deals with the construction and analysis of linear codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of algebraic structures such as abelian codes and the evaluation of weight distributions suggest that the paper may also belong to the coding theory sub-category (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the minimum distance of the dual code, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The application of the codes in secret sharing schemes suggests that the paper may also belong to the distributed systems sub-category (cs.DS) or the security and privacy sub-category (cs.SI).
